    <text type="petition">
        <body>            
            
            <!-- Begins with the text of the petition. -->
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.00995.001.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="petition" corresp="#rg21">                
                
                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName> <choice><abbr>Esq</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> Clerk Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>—</salute>
                        <salute>Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>                    
                    <p>Mrs <persName>Alfred Scott</persName> of <placeName>Georgetown D.C.</placeName> having claim to the service or labor of the undersigned, and having refused or failed to file in your Office the statement or schedule provided for in the 9th section of the act of Congress entitled "An act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>." Approved <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date>.</p>
                    
                    <p>You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act approved <date when="1862-07-12">12th July 1862</date>. The undersigned resided in said <placeName>District</placeName> before and at the time of the passage of said supplemental act with said owners consent.</p>
                        <table>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Name</cell>
                                <cell>Sex</cell>
                                <cell>Age</cell>
                                <cell>Description</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Margaret Vaughn</cell>
                                <cell>female</cell>
                                <cell>nineteen years</cell>
                                <cell>Light Mulatto</cell>
                            </row>                           
                        </table>                  
                    
                    <closer>
                        <signed><persName>Margaret Vaughn</persName></signed><lb/>
                        
                        Witness<lb/>
                        <persName>Jno. M. Hanson</persName>
                    </closer>
                </div3>
                
             
              </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.00995.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Paid $..50</ab>
                        <ab><persName>Margaret Vaughn</persName></ab>
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-09-24">24th Sept 1862</date></ab>
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folios 109 &amp; 110</ab>
                    </div3>
                    
                   <div3 type="section">
                       <ab>The Commissioners, satisfied on the testimony of Messrs. <persName>Josiah Dent</persName> &amp; <persName>J.C. Marbury</persName>, <choice><abbr>Atts</abbr><expan>Attorneys</expan></choice> at Law, of the truth of the within statement, order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>Dist. of Columbia</placeName></ab>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName></signed><lb/> Clerk <choice><abbr>Eman.</abbr><expan>Emancipation</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>Comn</abbr><expan>Commission</expan></choice>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-09-26">1862, 26 Sept</date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                   </div3>
                </div2>
                
            </div1>
            
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="cww.00995.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                
                <dateline><date when="1862-09-26">September 26th 1862</date></dateline>
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Margaret Vaughan</persName></ab>
                    <ab>Servant of Mrs. <persName>Alfred Scott</persName> or <persName>Rebecca B Scott</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">                   
                    <ab><persName>Josiah Dent</persName>. Summoned.</ab> 
                    <ab>I know all the facts stated in the Schedule to be true as stated To my knowledge <persName>Mrs Scott</persName> owned this servant. <persName>Mrs Scott</persName> left here more than a year ago for the south leaving this servant to take care of herself. She made some provision through me for the servant which I attended to.</ab>
                    <ab>The servant was here by <persName>Mrs Scotts</persName> consent.</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <ab><persName>J. Carter Marbury</persName> (summoned) I know the facts as stated  by <persName>Mr Dent</persName>. <persName>Mrs Scott</persName> who had a brother in <placeName> Alabama</placeName>, where she came from, left her at the beginning of the <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">troubles</unclear> leaving the servant <persName>Margaret</persName> who was maid for <persName>Mrs Scotts</persName> daughter. <persName>Mrs Scott</persName> had set aunt of <persName>Margaret</persName> free.</ab>
                    <ab>Servant was here by <persName>Mrs Scotts</persName> consent</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><choice><abbr>Cert</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> ordered &amp; sent</ab>
                </div2>               
               
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="cww.00995.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover">                    
                    <ab><persName>Margt Vaughan<lb/>
                    Margaret</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-09-26">September 26</date>.</ab>                    
                </div2>
            
            </div1>            
        </body>
    </text>
